<br>
A manager at a fast food resturant was told that the girl taking her order was rude to her.  The manager apologized and said that she would speak with the employee.  The manager spoke with the girl and as it turns out, the customer was very rude to her.  The manager took the employee's word and knew that it most likely wouldn't happen again, she had been warned.  There was another complaint about the girl a week later, but this time about service.  There were a few complaints here an there about her, on with her forgetting to put fries on the tray, and one where she didn't make the order to go when it was supposed to be eaten in the resturnat.  Did the manager speak to her about it?  No, in that line of work you have to learn that customers are always going to complain, there will always be someone who is unhappy, and that there will always be mistakes.<br>
<br>
A new guy got hired a little while after that.  He too got a complaint about his attitude.  As always his boss asked him what happened and his boss gave him the benefit of the doubt that it wasn't the employee's fault, and if it was he had been warned.  A few days later there was a complaint about his attitude again.  The boss didn't ask him what happened and ignored it.  After a few more complaints in the next few weeks the manager asked the new guy why he had so many complaints?  The new guy gave some lame excuse of course.  After a few more complaints the new guy had to be fired.<br>
<br>
What's the difference between the guy and the girl?  The guy had made the same mistake again and again, AND was complained about by many different people.  Whereas the girls was a mistake here and there, and always something minor that she was improving on.<br>
<br>
My one complaint to them won't mean much, but if a lot of people complain and type them an e-mail once in a while maybe there will be something done to improve our situation.  That's still a maybe.  Our chances for success also improve if we all complain about the same thing.  In 90% of the things I've read, we want more HP's and the softcap to be moved for us, a defense mod and maybe a little more damage, but but not much.  Possibly getting a new skill, like protecting others would be helpful.  So by all means, send them complaints, and send them often.  Anytime you feel like you've been shafted because you're a warrior, write them.  If you're bored and have nothing to do, write them,  if you've just been killed by a mob because your sow left you when you were trying to run through a zone, write them, if you spent the night shouting LFG, write them.  You get the point.  It might not even help, but you've done your part to at least aggrivate the people who have aggrivate you. <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=294603 Profile </a>
